      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DONT WAIT FOR LUCK (2) jumped favourite last start and got the job done by 0.2L and drops back to the 1300m today. That shouldn't be an issue and he draws the inside with Fiore taking over from the apprentice. Can go back-to-back in this suitable assignment. DADIRRA (6) is better than she showed fresh when just out-paced over the 1100m journey. Up to this distance should suit her much better and she can be on the speed from the barrier. Tsang's claim comes in handy and she'll be tough to run down. TREASURED QUEEN (5) has been just fair in both runs back and steps out to 1300m now for just the third time. She boasts a strong third-up record however and if she can stretch in trip, she'll be in this for a long way. PRAWNS ELEVEN (1) is beginning to build a pattern with his form but 1300m is a new test for him. Hard to knock on his best efforts however. SCOTTISH LAIRD (9) can feature on resumption.",
